WEBVTT

00:06.000 --> 00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:12.815 --> 00:14.732
Hey! What are you doing?

00:18.895 --> 00:20.938
- Jesus.
- Did you get a good look?

00:20.856 --> 00:22.898
Blue Toyota camry.
That's all I saw.

00:22.814 --> 00:24.065
That's the Whartons' dog.

00:24.016 --> 00:25.766
Aw, man.

00:25.696 --> 00:28.407
He's not going to make it.
Go see if they're home.

00:35.577 --> 00:39.831
Shh. Shh.

00:39.657 --> 00:41.991
It's okay.

00:44.218 --> 00:46.512
There are two kinds of pain...

00:46.419 --> 00:48.628
The sort of pain that makes you strong,

00:48.538 --> 00:50.498
or useless pain,

00:50.419 --> 00:53.545
the sort of pain that's only suffering.

00:53.419 --> 00:56.672
I have no patience for useless things.

00:58.139 --> 01:01.141
Moments like this require
someone who will act,

01:01.019 --> 01:04.188
who will do the unpleasant thing,

01:04.059 --> 01:06.561
the necessary thing.

01:10.859 --> 01:12.278
There.

01:12.222 --> 01:14.014
No more pain.

01:15.820 --> 01:18.698
It was a hit-and-run.
I'm awfully sorry.

01:18.581 --> 01:20.707
He must have jumped
over the fence again.

01:20.622 --> 01:22.623
Look, Steve is going to file
the report on the car,

01:22.542 --> 01:24.209
and he'll put his people on it.

01:24.141 --> 01:26.058
We'll track them down.

01:44.944 --> 01:47.905
You look stunning. Shall we?

01:47.785 --> 01:50.286
Three, two, one...

01:50.184 --> 01:52.686
Happy new year!

01:58.545 --> 02:01.089
Oh. President-elect
Garrett Walker.

02:00.987 --> 02:02.529
Do I like him? No.

02:02.466 --> 02:04.301
Do I believe in him?
That's beside the point.

02:04.227 --> 02:06.435
Any politician
that gets 70 million votes

02:06.347 --> 02:08.556
has tapped into something
larger than himself...

02:08.466 --> 02:10.717
Larger than even me,
as much as I hate to admit it.

02:10.627 --> 02:13.587
And look at that winning smile,
those trusting eyes.

02:13.467 --> 02:16.469
I latched onto him early on
and made myself vital.

02:16.348 --> 02:18.265
After 22 years in congress,

02:18.188 --> 02:20.649
I can smell which way
the wind is blowing.

02:20.549 --> 02:22.049
Oh, Jim Matthews,

02:21.989 --> 02:23.698
his right honorable
vice-president.

02:23.629 --> 02:25.380
Former governor of Pennsylvania.

02:25.310 --> 02:27.686
He did his duty in delivering
the keystone state,

02:27.589 --> 02:29.090
bless his heart,

02:29.030 --> 02:30.864
and now they're about
to put him out to pasture.

02:30.790 --> 02:32.832
But he looks happy enough, doesn't he?

02:32.749 --> 02:36.878
For some, it's simply
the size of the chair.

02:36.711 --> 02:38.461
Huh.

02:38.390 --> 02:40.725
Linda vasquez, Walker's chief of staff.

02:40.631 --> 02:42.048
I got her hired.

02:41.990 --> 02:44.241
She's a woman, check,
and a latina, check,

02:44.150 --> 02:45.693
but more important than that,

02:45.632 --> 02:47.673
she's as tough
as a two-dollar steak.

02:47.590 --> 02:49.133
Check, check, check.

02:49.072 --> 02:50.614
When it comes to the white house,

02:50.551 --> 02:52.803
you not only need the keys
in your back pocket,

02:52.712 --> 02:54.254
you need the gatekeeper.

02:54.192 --> 02:56.860
As for me, I'm just
a lowly house majority whip.

02:56.751 --> 02:58.585
I keep things moving in a congress

02:58.512 --> 03:00.722
choked by pettiness and lassitude.

03:00.633 --> 03:03.802
My job is to clear the pipes
and keep the sludge moving.

03:03.673 --> 03:05.632
But I won't have to be
a plumber much longer.

03:05.552 --> 03:08.012
I've done my time.
I backed the right man.

03:08.913 --> 03:10.831
Happy new year!

03:10.753 --> 03:12.546
Give and take.

03:12.474 --> 03:14.557
Welcome to Washington.

04:48.724 --> 04:50.726
You need a haircut.

04:50.644 --> 04:52.061
You think?

04:52.004 --> 04:53.963
A little trim.

04:55.084 --> 04:56.752
What are you going to wear?

04:56.685 --> 04:58.936
- You mean for the meeting?
- For the announcement.

04:58.846 --> 05:01.807
Gonna wear my Navy blue,
the one with the pinstripes.

05:01.686 --> 05:04.855
Good. You look handsome
in that suit.

05:05.924 --> 05:07.510
I don't know if they'll announce it

05:07.446 --> 05:08.987
before your board meeting.

05:08.925 --> 05:10.593
Well, as long as I can say
the donation is coming.

05:10.526 --> 05:12.068
As soon as it's official,

05:12.006 --> 05:14.341
Sancorp will write you a check.

05:16.966 --> 05:20.136
This is going to be a big year for us.

05:33.489 --> 05:35.616
You know, the meeting's on Tuesday.

05:37.768 --> 05:39.437
You're gonna wanna
start with something...

05:39.370 --> 05:40.954
That's what I'm hearing.

05:40.890 --> 05:42.431
Community of what?

05:42.369 --> 05:44.663
Or I could say immigration,
banking, or education,

05:44.570 --> 05:46.905
but none of my regular sources
can confirm that.

05:46.811 --> 05:48.603
Because they don't know,

05:48.530 --> 05:50.239
or because they're not talking?

05:50.170 --> 05:51.629
Because they don't know.

05:51.571 --> 05:53.822
Keep at it. Get me something.

05:53.731 --> 05:56.733
Sorry.
Sorry, Mr. Hammerschmidt.

05:56.611 --> 05:58.904
Zoe.

05:58.811 --> 06:01.146
- Barnes.
- Right.

06:03.891 --> 06:06.227
Did it take him a year
to remember your name?

06:06.132 --> 06:07.132
Longer.

06:07.093 --> 06:09.301
Good morning, Lucas.

06:09.211 --> 06:10.629
What can I do for you, Zoe?

06:13.091 --> 06:15.302
I am sick of the Fairfax county council.

06:15.213 --> 06:16.798
You tell me every day.

06:16.735 --> 06:18.527
Move me online. My own blog...

06:18.453 --> 06:20.954
First person, subjective, 500 words.

06:20.853 --> 06:23.063
- Not going to happen.
- I'll go underground.

06:22.974 --> 06:24.475
Back rooms. The urinals.

06:24.414 --> 06:26.248
I'll win over staff members on the hill.

06:26.175 --> 06:28.259
- They need a place to vent.
- A gossip column.

06:28.175 --> 06:30.718
No. We lift the veil,
what's really going on.

06:30.614 --> 06:32.490
This is the Washington herald, Zoe.

06:32.415 --> 06:34.208
It's not TMZ.

06:34.136 --> 06:35.469
Do you know how many people watch TMZ?

06:35.415 --> 06:36.791
I couldn't care less.

06:36.735 --> 06:38.527
Which is why print journalism is dying.

06:38.456 --> 06:40.624
Then it'll die with dignity,
at least at this paper.

06:40.536 --> 06:43.580
You are stuck in the 20th century, Lucas.
You lack imagination.

06:43.457 --> 06:44.749
Maybe so, but right now,

06:44.697 --> 06:46.656
I don't need imagination.
I need copy.

06:46.577 --> 06:48.453
Your nights and weekends are yours.

06:48.377 --> 06:49.919
I applaud whatever you want to do,

06:49.858 --> 06:51.566
as long as it's not on my time.

06:51.496 --> 06:53.664
- You're telling me to get back to work.
- I am.

06:53.577 --> 06:56.454
What you're really telling me
is to fuck off.

06:56.338 --> 06:57.964
I'm telling you both.

07:00.777 --> 07:05.365
It's Mr. Chapman already
from province trust.

07:10.099 --> 07:12.143
Hold my calls, Christina.

07:13.698 --> 07:17.202
Henry. It's good to see you.

07:17.060 --> 07:19.144
- How long are you in town for?
- Just today.

07:19.060 --> 07:21.270
Well, you gotta come back down
for the inauguration.

07:21.181 --> 07:23.223
I can hook you up.

07:23.140 --> 07:25.349
How about you hook me up with the zoning
laws you promised to get changed?

07:25.260 --> 07:27.261
We got 12 million sitting in escrow

07:27.180 --> 07:29.056
for an empty lot we can't build on.

07:28.980 --> 07:30.690
I know, but you gotta understand,

07:30.622 --> 07:31.871
it's a local municipal issue.

07:31.820 --> 07:33.821
I can't just pick up the phone...

07:33.741 --> 07:36.243
You can't? Because that's not
what you led us to believe

07:36.141 --> 07:38.268
when you begged
for 50 grand in donations.

07:38.182 --> 07:40.975
Right. I...

07:40.862 --> 07:42.071
One second.

07:42.024 --> 07:43.440
Christina, I said no calls,

07:43.382 --> 07:45.592
not while I'm meeting
with Mr. Chapman.

07:47.181 --> 07:49.476
The president-elect?

07:50.663 --> 07:52.289
I... do you mind?

07:52.223 --> 07:53.473
No. Go ahead, please.

07:53.423 --> 07:55.257
Uh, put him through, Christina.

07:55.183 --> 07:56.684
Ahem.

07:58.944 --> 08:00.862
Mr. president-elect?

08:03.583 --> 08:05.877
Thank you.
Uh, yes, we were, uh...

08:05.785 --> 08:08.411
We were pleased to win by double digits.

08:09.304 --> 08:11.057
Absolutely. Anything you need.

08:10.986 --> 08:14.279
I need you to put your
long, wet, talented tongue

08:14.145 --> 08:15.729
between my thighs

08:15.667 --> 08:18.294
and make me squeal like Monica Lewin...

08:19.346 --> 08:22.141
Me, too. Me, too.

08:22.905 --> 08:24.865
Okay. Thank you, sir.

08:25.905 --> 08:28.867
I'm so sorry.
Uh, where were we?

08:29.986 --> 08:32.238
Walker...

08:32.148 --> 08:33.774
What's he like?

08:46.308 --> 08:48.310
Mr. president-elect
running late?

08:48.229 --> 08:50.980
No, he couldn't make it.
I'll brief him, though.

08:52.029 --> 08:54.489
Okay. This is the memo
I've drafted

08:54.389 --> 08:56.516
on our middle east policy
we've been developing.

08:56.430 --> 08:58.347
Now, I want to borrow from Reagan.

08:58.271 --> 09:00.982
I'd like to coin the phrase
"trickle-down diplomacy."

09:00.871 --> 09:03.915
- That way...
- Frank, I'm going to stop you there.

09:03.792 --> 09:06.668
We are not nominating you
for secretary of state.

09:06.551 --> 09:08.427
I know he made you a promise,

09:08.352 --> 09:10.103
but circumstances have changed.

09:10.032 --> 09:11.658
The nature of promises, Linda,

09:11.592 --> 09:14.885
is that they remain immune
to changing circumstances.

09:14.752 --> 09:17.087
Garrett has thought long
and hard about this,

09:16.993 --> 09:19.870
and he's decided we need you
to stay in congress.

09:19.754 --> 09:22.464
When was this decision made,

09:22.354 --> 09:24.730
and why wasn't I part
of the conversation?

09:24.632 --> 09:26.216
I'm sorry, Frank.
If it had been up to me,

09:26.153 --> 09:27.737
I wouldn't have waited
this long to tell you.

09:27.673 --> 09:29.966
So, you knew you were going to do this.

09:29.874 --> 09:31.750
It has been an evolving discussion.

09:31.674 --> 09:34.760
It's a chicken-shit move.

09:34.635 --> 09:36.010
- Frank...
- I was vetted.

09:35.955 --> 09:37.372
- Was that a ruse?
- No.

09:37.315 --> 09:38.606
Let's be absolutely clear.

09:38.554 --> 09:40.555
You wouldn't have won without me.

09:40.474 --> 09:42.226
You're right, but now we have to lead,

09:42.155 --> 09:44.698
and that means making tough choices.

09:44.596 --> 09:47.472
As you know, education
is a top priority for us,

09:47.355 --> 09:49.065
a complete federal overhaul.

09:48.996 --> 09:51.414
But it's not just education.
Frank, congress is split.

09:51.316 --> 09:55.694
We need you there more than we
need you in the state department.

09:55.516 --> 09:57.726
I got you hired, Linda.

09:59.036 --> 10:00.204
I know.

10:00.157 --> 10:01.533
Donations, endorsements.

10:01.477 --> 10:03.061
I wrote the campaign's

10:02.998 --> 10:04.999
entire foreign policy platform.

10:04.918 --> 10:07.378
I bring years of
foreign affairs committee...

10:07.278 --> 10:09.612
Frank, please.

10:11.958 --> 10:14.293
I want to speak to Walker personally.

10:14.199 --> 10:16.408
The decision is made.

10:19.958 --> 10:22.586
We need you, Frank.

10:22.479 --> 10:24.855
Will you stand beside us or not?

10:33.800 --> 10:36.136
Of course. If that's
what the president wants.

10:36.042 --> 10:39.377
I'm very glad to hear that.

10:40.441 --> 10:42.610
I'm curious.

10:42.522 --> 10:44.356
If not me, then who?

10:46.081 --> 10:47.707
Michael kern.

10:47.641 --> 10:49.351
Michael kern?

10:50.601 --> 10:52.395
Well...

10:52.322 --> 10:54.865
That is an excellent choice.

10:58.282 --> 10:59.826
Can you make it more clear?

10:59.764 --> 11:01.556
I just want to make sure
it doesn't look like

11:01.483 --> 11:03.108
we're neglecting our domestic...

11:03.044 --> 11:04.462
No. No, no, no.
I'm going to say

11:04.404 --> 11:06.029
that we're expanding our mission.

11:05.964 --> 11:07.757
Okay.

11:07.684 --> 11:10.102
And we're bringing on
a new organization to help us.

11:10.005 --> 11:11.589
Do you know which one yet?

11:11.525 --> 11:13.776
I'm still looking into
a few options, but, um,

11:13.685 --> 11:15.144
tell me, what did we agree on,

11:15.085 --> 11:17.670
that we could hire
how many new people? Six?

11:17.565 --> 11:19.066
- Six, maybe seven.
- Hmm?

11:19.006 --> 11:20.840
We'll have enough.

11:20.766 --> 11:22.474
Ooh, it's exciting, huh?

11:22.406 --> 11:25.534
This, uh, new direction we're heading.

11:25.406 --> 11:28.324
I just don't know where we're
going to fit all the people.

11:28.206 --> 11:30.249
Well, do you think we have
to look into additional space?

11:30.167 --> 11:31.917
No. No, no, no.
I'll find a way.

11:31.846 --> 11:33.514
Okay, so make the changes
to the PowerPoint,

11:33.447 --> 11:35.156
and let's meet again at 2:30.

11:35.087 --> 11:36.421
Okay.

11:43.769 --> 11:45.937
Leave a message
for Frank Underwood.

11:47.049 --> 11:48.549
It's me.

11:48.489 --> 11:50.532
I feel like an idiot
leaving messages like this.

11:50.448 --> 11:52.073
Call me back.

12:03.410 --> 12:04.535
What is it, Zoe?

12:04.490 --> 12:06.491
Um...

12:06.409 --> 12:08.536
I know you're going to have your
hands full at the white house,

12:08.451 --> 12:11.661
so if you need someone
to do research or...

12:11.531 --> 12:12.865
Or print out background...

12:12.811 --> 12:14.478
I think I'll be fine.

12:14.411 --> 12:16.997
Well, if things get hectic
and you need any help...

12:16.892 --> 12:21.103
So you can blog about rubbing
shoulders with the big boys?

12:23.771 --> 12:25.231
What did Lucas tell you?

12:25.173 --> 12:27.132
Look, no offense, Zoe,
but I don't have time

12:27.052 --> 12:29.304
to be anyone's training wheels.

12:29.214 --> 12:31.590
I just thought...

12:31.493 --> 12:34.120
No, I was actually offering
to lend a hand.

12:34.014 --> 12:35.764
- That's it.
- Got it.

12:35.694 --> 12:37.403
Thanks.

13:15.696 --> 13:17.573
- Claire.
- You didn't call.

13:17.498 --> 13:20.876
- I was...
- You didn't call me, Francis.

13:20.740 --> 13:23.200
Nine hours.
You don't not call me,

13:23.099 --> 13:24.766
not when it's this big.

13:24.699 --> 13:26.033
You're right.

13:25.979 --> 13:29.023
When have we ever avoided each other?

13:30.779 --> 13:32.781
I wanted the solution first.

13:32.701 --> 13:34.118
Do you have one?

13:34.060 --> 13:35.935
Not yet.

13:35.860 --> 13:37.903
This affects me, too, Francis.

13:37.819 --> 13:40.779
And it's not the money I'm upset about.

13:40.660 --> 13:43.329
It's that we do things together.

13:43.221 --> 13:45.889
When you don't involve me,
we're in free-fall.

13:45.781 --> 13:48.533
I should've called you, and I didn't.

13:48.421 --> 13:49.838
What happened?

13:51.141 --> 13:53.519
She says they needed
to keep me in congress.

13:53.422 --> 13:54.630
Linda said that?

13:54.581 --> 13:55.790
Walker wasn't even there.

13:55.743 --> 13:57.327
That's what really gets me.

13:57.263 --> 13:59.097
He didn't have the courage
to look me in the eye.

13:59.024 --> 14:00.774
I knew you shouldn't trust that woman.

14:00.702 --> 14:02.454
I didn't. I don't.
I don't trust anyone.

14:02.383 --> 14:04.550
Then how could you not see this coming?

14:05.943 --> 14:08.070
I never thought they were capable.

14:07.984 --> 14:10.860
You don't usually
underestimate people, Francis.

14:10.743 --> 14:12.036
I know.

14:13.424 --> 14:16.010
Hubris. Ambition.

14:15.904 --> 14:17.112
You should be angry.

14:17.065 --> 14:18.357
I'm livid.

14:18.304 --> 14:20.222
Then where is that?
I don't see it.

14:20.145 --> 14:22.438
What do you want me to do? Scream and yell?
Throw a tantrum?

14:22.345 --> 14:24.888
I want more than I'm seeing
. You're better than this, Francis.

14:24.785 --> 14:27.954
Well, I'm sorry, Claire.
I am sorry.

14:27.826 --> 14:29.618
No, that I won't accept.

14:29.546 --> 14:32.298
- What?
- Apologies.

14:34.345 --> 14:36.806
My husband doesn't apologize,

14:36.707 --> 14:38.833
even to me.

16:20.157 --> 16:21.784
How long you been up?

16:21.719 --> 16:23.428
Hours.

16:25.716 --> 16:27.927
I know what I have to do.

16:27.839 --> 16:29.465
Good.

16:29.399 --> 16:32.150
We'll have a lot of nights like this...

16:32.039 --> 16:35.792
Making plans, very little sleep.

16:35.639 --> 16:37.932
I expected that.

16:37.839 --> 16:40.382
It doesn't worry me.

16:48.879 --> 16:51.215
I'd better get to work.

16:51.121 --> 16:54.665
I laid a suit out for you upstairs.

16:54.522 --> 16:56.857
The Navy-blue one.

17:02.202 --> 17:03.704
I love that woman.

17:03.643 --> 17:05.853
I love her more than sharks love blood.

17:08.962 --> 17:10.838
President-elect
Garrett Walker has just...

17:10.762 --> 17:12.638
Why do you think
they went with him?

17:12.564 --> 17:15.273
We're too good. They can't
afford to lose us in congress.

17:15.164 --> 17:17.040
He's had work done.

17:16.964 --> 17:18.631
Chin tuck probably.

17:18.564 --> 17:19.731
Definitely dyes his hair.

17:21.404 --> 17:22.529
Do we say anything?

17:22.484 --> 17:23.903
No. God, no.

17:23.845 --> 17:25.637
Not unless he brings it up.

17:25.565 --> 17:27.190
Nancy!

17:27.124 --> 17:28.625
- 9:20...
- Cancel everything.

17:28.565 --> 17:30.775
Stamper, you're with me.

17:30.686 --> 17:32.311
Now, look...

17:33.605 --> 17:36.148
They've done us
a great favor, Doug.

17:36.045 --> 17:38.631
We are no longer bound by allegiances.

17:38.527 --> 17:40.236
We serve no one.

17:40.168 --> 17:42.419
We live by one rule and one rule only...

17:42.326 --> 17:44.327
Never again will we allow ourselves

17:44.247 --> 17:46.498
to be put in such a position.

17:46.408 --> 17:47.783
Walker and vasquez.

17:47.727 --> 17:50.855
All of them.
I hold them all accountable.

17:50.728 --> 17:53.187
- Want retribution?
- No. No.

17:53.088 --> 17:55.673
It's more than that.

17:55.568 --> 17:57.986
Take a step back.

17:57.888 --> 17:59.598
Look at the bigger picture.

17:59.529 --> 18:02.322
I think I see what you're getting at.

18:02.209 --> 18:03.543
Kern first?

18:03.488 --> 18:05.613
That's how you devour a whale, Doug...

18:05.528 --> 18:07.238
One bite at a time.

18:07.169 --> 18:09.419
Who would you want
for secretary of state?

18:09.329 --> 18:10.956
Give me a list of choices.

18:10.890 --> 18:14.100
And however we do this,
we'll also need a buffer.

18:13.969 --> 18:15.386
You mean an errand boy.

18:15.330 --> 18:17.790
Yes, someone we control completely.

18:18.889 --> 18:20.641
I'll keep my ear to the ground.

18:20.571 --> 18:22.029
Good.

18:21.970 --> 18:24.889
I haven't eaten since yesterday.

18:42.252 --> 18:44.087
I almost pity him.

18:44.013 --> 18:46.055
He didn't choose
to be put on my platter.

18:45.973 --> 18:48.308
When I carve him up
and toss him to the dogs,

18:48.213 --> 18:52.258
only then will he confront that
brutal, inescapable truth...

18:52.093 --> 18:54.011
"My God.

18:53.934 --> 18:57.519
All I ever amounted to
was chitlins."

18:57.374 --> 19:00.252
And he that shall humble himself

