How do you expect me to get
that through a committee?

37:34.413 --> 37:36.206
When Linda told me
to write it, she promised...

37:36.134 --> 37:37.760
I'm sure she said any number of things.

37:37.694 --> 37:39.319
Forget what they promised you, Donald.

37:39.254 --> 37:42.256
They want your name
because it carries weight.

37:42.134 --> 37:43.843
Well, my name comes with my ideas.

37:43.774 --> 37:45.566
I understand, but you've
got to be reasonable.

37:45.494 --> 37:46.870
This isn't the great debate.

37:46.815 --> 37:49.192
It's about passing meaningful reform.

37:49.096 --> 37:53.473
Maybe not everything you would've
hoped, but help me help you.

37:53.295 --> 37:55.129
That's going to take time.

37:55.054 --> 37:56.889
I... those ideas, I've
been developing them for...

37:56.816 --> 37:59.150
If it's time you need,
I will buy you time,

37:59.055 --> 38:01.015
but you've got to promise me
your next-at-bat

38:00.937 --> 38:04.189
is going to give me something
I can work with.

38:04.057 --> 38:06.642
Okay, Frank, I'll see what I can do.

38:06.537 --> 38:08.830
Good. And, Donald, don't let
this get you down, all right?

38:08.737 --> 38:14.575
Together we're going to do more than
you've been able to do in 25 years.

38:16.938 --> 38:18.773
Two things are now irrelevant...

38:18.699 --> 38:21.241
Donald blythe
and Donald Blythe's new draft.

38:21.137 --> 38:23.347
Eventually I'll have
to rewrite the bill myself.

38:23.258 --> 38:25.176
Forward!
That is the battle cry.

38:25.099 --> 38:27.392
Leave ideology to the armchair generals.

38:27.299 --> 38:29.175
It does me no good.

38:29.100 --> 38:31.726
Walker just nominated kern.

38:31.619 --> 38:34.330
It's a long road to confirmation.

38:34.221 --> 38:37.014
- Kern is a boy scout.
- Nobody's a boy scout.

38:36.901 --> 38:38.610
Not even boy scouts.

38:39.418 --> 38:40.753
What do you have?

38:40.701 --> 38:42.535
Absolutely nothing.

38:43.942 --> 38:45.609
Then what are we talking about?

38:45.541 --> 38:47.083
Just asking a simple question.

38:47.022 --> 38:48.815
Does the job interest you?

38:50.221 --> 38:52.848
Why would you want Michael gone?

38:52.743 --> 38:54.786
Cathy, you and I came up together.

38:54.701 --> 38:56.869
The foreign affairs committee needs
a secretary we can work with,

38:56.783 --> 39:00.286
someone who isn't afraid to stand
up to Walker when he's wrong.

39:00.143 --> 39:02.393
We need you.

39:06.302 --> 39:08.388
Let's assume I am interested.

39:08.303 --> 39:10.053
I don't want to assume.

39:09.982 --> 39:12.651
I want to know.

39:53.147 --> 39:54.900
2...Okay.

39:54.829 --> 39:56.204
2-6-3-7.

40:01.708 --> 40:03.543
Please hold.

40:03.470 --> 40:05.387
Zoe Barnes.

40:06.628 --> 40:10.216
Anywhere you want. On my way.

40:10.071 --> 40:12.280
I'm gonna have to call you back.

40:25.591 --> 40:28.719
So sorry. I couldn't catch a cab.
I had to take a train...

40:28.592 --> 40:30.634
Just before you left my house...

40:30.553 --> 40:32.221
Think back...

40:32.154 --> 40:33.946
What were we discussing?

40:35.032 --> 40:36.741
The president's legislative agenda.

40:36.673 --> 40:38.591
Specifically.

40:38.512 --> 40:40.638
Education. Was I right?

40:40.553 --> 40:43.179
Do the math, miss Barnes.

40:43.073 --> 40:46.284
- He needs a bill.
- Sponsored by...

40:46.154 --> 40:49.866
- You?
- Be smarter than that.

40:51.834 --> 40:53.628
- Somebody with legitimacy.
- Good.

40:53.555 --> 40:56.806
And who screams legitimacy
and education?

40:56.674 --> 40:59.551
- Donald blythe?
- Correct. The problem is...

40:59.435 --> 41:02.395
He's an old-school
tax-and-spend liberal.

41:02.275 --> 41:04.986
Walker ran as a moderate.

41:06.195 --> 41:08.573
You think blythe would talk to me?

41:09.436 --> 41:11.563
He doesn't have to.

41:12.956 --> 41:15.375
Wait. We're in
a very gray area...

41:15.277 --> 41:18.029
Ethically, legally...
Which I'm okay with...

41:17.918 --> 41:20.503
I just love this painting.
Don't you?

41:21.877 --> 41:24.296
We're in the same boat now, Zoe.

41:24.197 --> 41:25.739
Take care not to tip it over.

41:25.678 --> 41:28.638
I can only save one of us from drowning.

41:54.119 --> 41:56.622
He announces his education
initiative on Monday.

41:56.522 --> 41:58.941
- Half of the address is based on...
- I understand.

41:58.842 --> 42:01.176
- Do we need to take it out?
- We're fine, Linda.

42:01.082 --> 42:03.542
But you just got through
saying he has to start over.

42:03.442 --> 42:05.401
I didn't choose blythe.
You did.

42:05.322 --> 42:08.074
You put him in my lap and asked
me to work a miracle, and I will.

42:07.963 --> 42:10.006
Now, have a little faith, Linda.

42:09.923 --> 42:11.506
Let me work with Donald on this.

42:11.443 --> 42:14.154
I know what can be
accomplished in 100 days.

42:14.044 --> 42:17.088
All right, Frank.
We're counting on you.

42:16.965 --> 42:18.673
Good.

42:19.924 --> 42:21.884
Now, I do have a little favor to ask.

42:21.804 --> 42:25.223
Do you think I can get
just two more tickets

42:25.084 --> 42:28.420
for my table at the Jefferson ball?

42:37.765 --> 42:41.268
- Drink?
- Uh, sure! What do you got?

42:41.126 --> 42:42.543
Whiskey. Blend.

42:42.486 --> 42:45.321
If you're offering.

42:45.206 --> 42:47.917
So... how are things

42:47.808 --> 42:49.558
in the city of brotherly love?

42:49.487 --> 42:52.281
- We're getting by.
- Oh, good.

42:52.168 --> 42:54.252
Good. Oh, I'm sorry.

42:54.168 --> 42:57.254
- I made that neat. Did you want...
- No, this is perfect.

43:06.528 --> 43:10.866
So, it seems you've been
a bit irresponsible.

43:10.690 --> 43:12.440
What?

43:12.370 --> 43:14.455
Don't play dumb with me, Peter.

43:14.370 --> 43:16.496
Save it for the ethics committee.

43:17.849 --> 43:20.519
Drink up. You could use
a little courage right now.

43:20.410 --> 43:22.911
You're not having one.

43:22.810 --> 43:26.063
It's a bit early in the day for me.

43:27.651 --> 43:29.986
Is this about the other night?

43:29.892 --> 43:31.308
How do you know about that?

43:31.251 --> 43:34.044
I'm the whip.
It's my job to know.

43:33.931 --> 43:35.725
Look... look, they let me off.

43:35.652 --> 43:38.612
There's... there's no charges.
It's all taken care of.

43:38.492 --> 43:40.493
Honestly, Peter,

43:40.413 --> 43:42.122
do you really think these things

43:42.053 --> 43:43.970
just take care of themselves?

43:43.892 --> 43:46.560
You...

43:48.654 --> 43:51.363
It was just this one time,
Frank. I swear to God.

43:51.253 --> 43:53.463
Then you must hold God
in very low esteem,

43:53.374 --> 43:56.585
because we both know that's a lie.

43:56.454 --> 43:59.957
"Solicitation, controlled substances,

43:59.814 --> 44:02.190
driving under the influence."

44:02.095 --> 44:04.888
Got quite a long list of hobbies.

44:06.095 --> 44:08.556
What is it you want?

44:18.335 --> 44:24.008
Your absolute, unquestioning loyalty.

44:23.778 --> 44:25.278
Always.

44:25.217 --> 44:29.220
Do not misunderstand
what I mean by "loyalty."

44:29.057 --> 44:31.976
Anything. Name it, Frank.

44:31.858 --> 44:35.444
- You seem far too relaxed.
- I'm not.

44:35.299 --> 44:37.508
You shouldn't be.

44:39.178 --> 44:41.513
Doug'll be in touch.

44:45.460 --> 44:46.835
Hang on.

44:46.781 --> 44:48.741
Where have you been?
I've been calling you.

44:48.660 --> 44:50.577
Everybody's working double-time
in an inauguration,

44:50.501 --> 44:53.002
and you just up and disappear...

44:53.899 --> 44:56.318
Hang on.

45:01.701 --> 45:03.453
Let me call you back.

45:06.741 --> 45:09.159
- Where did you get this?
- Wrong question.

45:09.062 --> 45:12.649
The right question is, how quickly
can we get it up on the site?

45:12.502 --> 45:15.170
I have to run this past tom.

45:15.063 --> 45:16.855
Let's get legal on this.

45:16.783 --> 45:19.160
Make sure we're not breaking any laws.

45:19.063 --> 45:21.605
- You won't tell me your source?
- I can't do that.

45:21.502 --> 45:24.171
- Fine, but if legal finds even one...
- I understand.

45:24.064 --> 45:26.732
How long do you think that will take?
We should get this online right away.

45:26.624 --> 45:28.667
I'm not just going to scan
a 300-page document

45:28.584 --> 45:30.376
and put it up before we
have gone through every...

45:30.304 --> 45:33.057
- I did that already.
- The whole thing?

45:32.945 --> 45:35.070
Cover to cover.
I've got excerpts, analysis.

45:34.984 --> 45:37.319
3,000 words ready for editing.

45:38.706 --> 45:40.165
You start going over them.

45:40.105 --> 45:42.231
Get graphics. Work on
the tables, charts...

45:42.145 --> 45:44.772
The whole nine yards.

45:44.666 --> 45:46.499
Janine!

45:46.426 --> 45:48.387
What's the angle? Five words.

45:48.307 --> 45:50.474
- Far left of center.
- That's four.

45:50.386 --> 45:53.138
- Very far left of center.
- Enough to put Walker on his heels?

45:53.026 --> 45:54.652
Fuck his heels.
This'll put him on his ass.

45:54.588 --> 45:56.463
What's up?

45:56.387 --> 45:59.222
We've got a copy of the
administration's education bill.

45:59.106 --> 46:01.775
- You're going to work with Zoe and do background cover.
- Zoe Barnes?

46:01.667 --> 46:04.544
- Right here.
- Whatever she needs.

46:04.428 --> 46:06.846
- Well, shouldn't I be writing the...
- She wrote it already.

46:06.748 --> 46:09.124
And I want you to rewrite it,
then rewrite it again.

46:09.028 --> 46:11.738
- You'll help her.
- Tom, I am your chief political correspondent.

46:11.628 --> 46:13.671
Go! I want this by tomorrow.

46:13.589 --> 46:16.091
- But I need to focus on the inauguration.
- This is more important.

46:15.990 --> 46:18.158
Let's get started.

46:18.070 --> 46:20.111
"That I will
faithfully execute the office"

46:20.029 --> 46:21.865
of president
of the United States."

46:21.791 --> 46:23.792
That I will faithfully
execute the office...

46:23.710 --> 46:25.544
Power is a lot like real estate.

46:25.471 --> 46:28.889
It's all about location,
location, location.

46:28.749 --> 46:30.584
The closer you are to the source,

46:30.512 --> 46:32.221
the higher your property value.

46:32.151 --> 46:34.110
"And defend
the constitution..."

46:34.031 --> 46:36.824
Centuries from now,
when people watch this footage,

46:36.712 --> 46:39.923
who will they see smiling
just at the edge of the frame?

46:39.792 --> 46:42.460
- "So help me God."
- So help me God.

46:42.351 --> 46:44.227
Congratulations.

47:00.033 --> 47:04.453
Today... is not about
the next four years.

47:04.274 --> 47:07.527
It's about the next four decades.

47:07.394 --> 47:10.229
Now, you've placed your faith in me,

47:10.115 --> 47:12.116
and I, in turn,

47:12.035 --> 47:15.996
choose to place that faith
in our children.

47:15.835 --> 47:20.964
Our children are the key
to this nation's future.

47:20.756 --> 47:23.342
And that's why
the first order of business

47:23.237 --> 47:24.945
for this administration

47:24.876 --> 47:28.545
will be a comprehensive
education reform bill

47:28.396 --> 47:32.190
to properly fix, finance,

47:32.036 --> 47:35.289
and strengthen our nation's schools!

47:37.956 --> 47:40.500
And I pledge to you,

47:40.399 --> 47:43.610
we will have that bill
on the floor of the congress

47:43.479 --> 47:47.899
within the first 100 days
of this administration!

47:52.920 --> 47:55.339
It was so nice of you
to make this possible.

47:55.239 --> 47:57.032
- When you called me, I was...
- Oh, not another one.

47:56.961 --> 47:58.711
I'm gonna miss out

47:58.640 --> 48:01.225
on my ultimate frisbee league this week.

48:01.120 --> 48:03.538
No, I'm serious.
A few of us on budget

48:03.441 --> 48:06.402
have quite a rivalry going
with the guys on finance.

48:06.281 --> 48:08.907
It's fierce. We get physical.

48:08.801 --> 48:10.718
Anybody gets between me
and that goal line,

48:10.641 --> 48:13.894
I will take that sucker down!

48:33.083 --> 48:35.710
Donald, I've been looking
for you everywhere.

48:35.603 --> 48:38.064
Maestro, here, let me
help you out with this.

48:37.964 --> 48:40.132
I really like the work
you've done on the new draft.

48:40.045 --> 48:42.546
It's a big step forward. We're
gonna make history together.

48:42.446 --> 48:44.530
Thanks for the encouragement.
Francis, listen...

48:44.445 --> 48:46.738
I've got some ideas about
subsidies for higher education...

48:46.644 --> 48:49.354
Catherine! Hold onto
that thought, Donald.

48:49.245 --> 48:52.205
Don't you look stunt!

48:52.085 --> 48:54.962
We Southern girls clean up well
when we get out of our Daisy Dukes

48:54.846 --> 48:58.099
- and into some vera wang.
- And we Southern boys are slow with our words,

48:57.967 --> 48:59.842
but we're fast on our feet.

48:59.767 --> 49:01.518
May I have the honor?

49:01.447 --> 49:03.615
You most certainly may.

49:27.169 --> 49:29.462
- Mornin', Freddy.
- Good morning, Frank.

49:29.368 --> 49:31.870
- How's tricks?
- I can't kick.

49:31.769 --> 49:34.604
- You want to go on in?
- No. Why don't you set me up outside?

49:34.490 --> 49:36.742
Outside?
It's freezing out here.

49:36.651 --> 49:39.235
Well, a little cold never hurt anybody.

49:39.130 --> 49:41.173
Anything you say, Frank.

49:41.091 --> 49:43.343
It'll be right up.

49:43.252 --> 49:46.462
My one guilty pleasure is a good rack
of ribs, even at 7:30 in the morning.

49:46.332 --> 49:48.208
Have the whole place to myself.

49:48.131 --> 49:49.798
Freddy sometimes opens up just for me.

49:49.732 --> 49:51.984
Where I come from in South Carolina,

49:51.893 --> 49:54.394
people didn't have
two pennies to rub together.

49:54.292 --> 49:57.294
A rack of ribs is a luxury, like...

50:00.212 --> 50:03.131
Christmas in July.

50:39.295 --> 50:41.840
This web traffic's absolutely crazy.

50:45.376 --> 50:49.422
Blue Camry, D.C.
Plate number whiskey, Juliet, 0-0-2-niner

50:49.258 --> 50:51.842
is wanted in connection
to a canine hit-and-run.

50:51.737 --> 50:54.739
Code 1057, found on capital...

50:54.618 --> 50:55.994
Mmm.

50:55.939 --> 50:57.399
Do you want seconds, Frank?

50:57.339 --> 50:59.631
I'd better not.

51:00.458 --> 51:02.585
Tell you what, Freddy...

51:02.499 --> 51:04.751
Yes, I will.

51:04.660 --> 51:07.704
I'm feeling hungry today.

